By Stef &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.freejazzblog.org/2009/06/fred-anderson-staying-in-game-esp-2009.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.freejazzblog.org/2009/06/fred-anderson-staying-in-game-esp-2009.html&lt;/a&gt;

Still going strong at the age of 80. It's not given to many, and yet he keeps
doing it, really going strong. Yes, he plays his signature style of warm,
soulful free jazz, that still has the joy and rhythmic nervousness of bop
somewhere in them, and he is a wonderful listener too, open to new sounds and
approaches. His sound is excellent, his improvisations are emotional, spritual
and focused. His companions are great too: Harrisson Bankhead on bass and Tim
Daisy on drums. True, he is not breaking any boundaries anymore, but with his
achievements and track record, any of his performances at this level are a joy
to hear. So, relax, sit down and enjoy the music.

--

